ReallyMe Crypto wraps third-party cryptographic implementations and platform
providers. Dependency license terms are recorded in the package manifests and
enforced by the repository dependency policy. Current provider families include
RustCrypto crates, ed25519-dalek, x25519-dalek, ml-kem, ml-dsa, BouncyCastle,
Bitcoin Core libsecp256k1 through reallyme/CSecp256k1 (Swift) and ACINQ
secp256k1-kmp (Kotlin/JVM), CryptoKit, JCA/JCE, @noble/curves, and
@noble/hashes.

